DESCRIPTION:Eighth Sunday after Pentecost\n\nLessons and Psalm:\n\n        
 Deuteronomy 30:9-14\n\n        Colossians 1:1-14\n\n        Luke 10:25-37\n
 \n        Psalm 25\n\nSupplemental Lectionary:\n\n        Deuteronomy 24:17
 -22\n\n        Romans 12:9-21\n\n        \n\nPrayer of the Day:\n\nAlmighty
  God\, we thank you for planting in us the seed of your Word.  By your Holy
  Spirit help us to receive it with joy and to bring forth fruits in faith a
 nd hope and love\; through your Son\, Jesus Christ our Lord\, who lives and
  reigns with you and the Holy Spirit\, one God\, now and forever.\n\nVerse 
