DESCRIPTION:Good Friday \n\nLessons and Psalm:\n      Isaiah 52:13--53:12\n
       Hebrews 4:14-16\; 5:7-9\n      John 19:17-30\n      Psalm 22 \n\nPray
 er of the Day: \n\nGod Most Holy\, look with mercy on this your family for 
 whom our Lord Jesus Christ was willing to be betrayed\, be given over into 
 the hands of the wicked\, and suffer death upon the cross.  Keep us always 
 faithful to him\, our only Savior\, who lives and reigns with you and the H
 oly Spirit\, one God\, now and forever.\n\nVerse of the Day: \n\nSurely he 
 took up our infirmities and carried our sorrows\, yet we considered him str
 icken by God\, smitten by him\, and afflicted.  (Isaiah 53:4)\n\nHymn of th
 e Day:\n      100     A Lamb Goes Uncomplaining Forth or\n      140       G
 od Was There on Calvary \n\nColor:  Black \n\n
